        h2#creating-advanced-layouts-with-the-bootstrap-card-component
          | Creating Advanced Layouts with the Bootstrap Card Component
        p
          | The card is a modern UI component that&apos;s utilized in many websites as a way to display items of mixed and different content types (such as text and images etc.) as a single/grouped entity, but more commonly as a collection of similar items with a different or the same width and height. A popular layout where cards can be used is the 
          a(href='https://www.sitepoint.com/understanding-masonry-layout/', target='_blank') Masonry layout
          | , also called the Pinterest-like Layout
        p.image-wrapper
