          code .card-columns
          |  class. That&apos;s all we need to do and Bootstrap will take care of the rest without having to use a JavaScript/jQuery plugin.
        p
          | Bootstrap uses CSS columns to create the Masonry-like layout where cards are added from top to bottom and left to right. However, if we need a 
          a(href='https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/issues/17882', target='_blank') different kind of behavior
          |  based on some algorithm, we&apos;ll have to resort to a JavaScript library or a jQuery plugin like 
          a(href='https://masonry.desandro.com/', target='_blank') Masonry
